text: The Queen of Italy Elena (also known as The Queen of Italy Elena ) was painted in oil by the italian painter Giuseppe Amisani, in 1925, is kept in the Collezione Farnesina of foreign minister of the Italian government in Rome from 1925.Elena Regina d'Italia, Stanza n. 1061 Cerimoniale III == Related pages == * Giuseppe Amisani * King of Italy Vittorio Emanuele III (Amisani) ==References== ==Other websites== * * Elena Regina d'Italia, Stanza n. 1061 Cerimoniale III Category:1920s paintings Category:Rome Category:Paintings by Giuseppe Amisani
title: The Queen of Italy Elena
